National Security Advisor Susan E. Rice will be traveling to China from July 24-27. In Beijing, she will meet with senior government officials and discuss various bilateral, regional, and global issues ahead of President Obama's visit to China in September. In Shanghai, Rice will meet with business executives to discuss the conditions for U.S. businesses operating in China. She will also interact with private Chinese citizens during her visit. The purpose of the trip is to emphasize the United States' commitment to expanding practical cooperation and managing differences with China. This will be Rice's fourth trip to China as National Security Advisor.